{"warnings":{"parse":{"*":"The value passed for \"page\" contains invalid or non-normalized data. Textual data should be valid, NFC-normalized Unicode without C0 control characters other than HT (\\t), LF (\\n), and CR (\\r)."}},"parse":{"title":"Elo\u00edna Miyares Berm\u00fadez","pageid":52740711,"revid":779139518,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox biography vcard\" style=\"width:22em\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold\"><span class=\"fn\">Eloina Miyares Bermudez</span></th></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Born</th><td>\n1928<br /><span class=\"birthplace\"><a href=\"/wiki/Santiago_de_Cuba\" title=\"Santiago de Cuba\">Santiago de Cuba</a></span></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Died</th><td>\n2015<br /><span class=\"deathplace\">Santiago de Cuba</span></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Nationality</th><td class=\"category\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/Cubans\" title=\"Cubans\">Cuban</a></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Eloina Miyares Bermudez</b> (1928 &#8211; July 26, 2015)<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> was a Cuban <a href=\"/wiki/Linguist\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Linguist\">linguist</a> and academician. She led the creation of the <i><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Diccionario_B%C3%A1sico_Escolar&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Diccionario B\u00e1sico Escolar (page does not exist)\">Diccionario B\u00e1sico Escolar</a></i> (DBE; Cuban basic school dictionary) from its first edition in 2005 until its fourth edition (digital in 2013 and paper in January 2015).<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>  The <i>Diccionario B\u00e1sico Escolar</i> is one of the books with the greatest circulation in Cuba.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Biography\">Biography</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Elo%C3%ADna_Miyares_Berm%C3%BAdez&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Biography\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Eloina Miyares Bermudez studied at the Escuela Normal de Oriente, from which she graduated in 1947. She first served as a teacher of rural areas in the municipality of <a href=\"/wiki/Palma_Soriano\" title=\"Palma Soriano\">Palma Soriano</a>, where she participated in the literacy campaign. She then studied at the Faculty of Humanities of the <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Santiago_de_Cuba\" title=\"University of Santiago de Cuba\">University of Santiago de Cuba</a>, graduating with a degree in Letters. She taught at the university until 1972 when she became a researcher at the Center of Applied Linguistics of the Academy of Sciences. She studied <a href=\"/wiki/Acoustic_phonetics\" title=\"Acoustic phonetics\">acoustic phonetics</a> at the Institute of the <a href=\"/wiki/Czech_Academy_of_Sciences\" title=\"Czech Academy of Sciences\">Czech Academy of Sciences</a> in <a href=\"/wiki/Prague\" title=\"Prague\">Prague</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>With her husband, <a href=\"/wiki/Philologist\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Philologist\">philologist</a> <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Julio_Vitelio_Ruiz_Hern%C3%A1ndez&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Julio Vitelio Ruiz Hern\u00e1ndez (page does not exist)\">Julio Vitelio Ruiz Hern\u00e1ndez</a>, she created a methodology for teachers and students to improve their pronunciation and spelling. The couple also founded the Center for Applied Linguistics of Santiago de Cuba (CLA) in 1971.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Bermudez had at least seven sons, including Dr. Leonel Miyares Ruiz.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rojas_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rojas-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Selected_works\">Selected works</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Elo%C3%ADna_Miyares_Berm%C3%BAdez&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Selected works\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li>1998, <i>Diccionario escolar ilustrado</i></li>\n<li>1999, <i>Vacuna ortogr\u00e1fica VAL-CUBA&#160;: nivel primario&#160;: metodolog\u00eda para prevenir y erradicar las faltas de ortograf\u00eda</i></li>\n<li>2000, <i>En torno al sustantivo y adjetivo en el espa\u00f1ol actual</i></li>\n<li>2003, <i>Diccionario b\u00e1sico escolar</i></li>\n<li>2006, <i>L\u00e9xico activo-funcional del escolar cubano</i></li>\n<li>2006, <i>Linguistics in the twenty first century</i></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Elo%C3%ADna_Miyares_Berm%C3%BAdez&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.ehu.eus/ehusfera/ixa/page/3/\">\"Elo\u00edna Miyares, the mother of the Cuban Basic School Dictionary\"</a>. <i>Ixa Group Language Technology: News from the Ixa Group in the University of the Basque Country</i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">17 April</span> 2017</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=Ixa+Group+Language+T